{"lemma":"مَنْبُوذٌ","slug":"مَنْبُوذٌ","root":"ن.ب.ذ","root_slug":"ن-ب-ذ","root_link":"/words/roots/ن-ب-ذ","pos":"ADJ","pos_camel":"adj","paradigm":[],"frequency_in_corpus":0,"cross_references":{"qac":{"found":false},"wiktextract":{"found":true,"entry_count":2,"pos_tags":["adj","noun"],"has_etymology":true,"sense_count":4},"lanes":{"found":true,"entry_ids":["n39218"],"search_url":"https://lanelexicon.com/?s=%D9%85%D9%8E%D9%86%D9%92%D8%A8%D9%8F%D9%88%D8%B0%D9%8C"}},"translations":null,"definition":{"source":"wiktextract","senses":[{"pos":"adj","gloss":"passive participle of نَبَذَ (nabaḏa, “to reject”); abandoned, deserted, rejected"},{"pos":"adj","gloss":"passive participle of نَبَذَ (nabaḏa, “to reject”); ostracized"},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"outcast, castaway"},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"foundling"}]},"etymology":{"source":"wiktextract","text":"Derived from the passive participle of the verb نَبَذَ (nabaḏa, “to reject”)."},"ipa":["/man.buːð/"],"lanes_definition":{"source":"lanes","entries":[{"entry_id":"n39218","headword_ar":"مَنْبُوذٌ","root":"nb*","body":[{"kind":"italic_en","text":"A child cast out by its mother"},{"kind":"text","text":"(T, S, L, Msb, K)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"in the road,"},{"kind":"text","text":"(T, S, L, K,)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"on the occasion of her bringing it forth, and which a Muslim picks up and maintains; whether a bastard"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"lawfully begotten;"},{"kind":"text","text":"(T, L;)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"a foundling:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(L, K:) such may not be called a bastard because its kin may be established: (T, L:) also, (assumed tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"a bastard;"},{"kind":"text","text":"(L, K;) because such is cast away in the road: (L:) fem."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"manobuw*apN","text_ar":"مَنْبُوذَةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"(L) and ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"nabiy*apN","text_ar":"نَبِيذَةٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":": (A, L:) pl. masc."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"manobuw*uwna","text_ar":"مَنْبُوذُونَ"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"manaAbi*apN","text_ar":"مَنَابِذَةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"; (L;) and pl: of"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"nby*p","text_ar":"نبيذة"},{"kind":"text","text":","},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"nabaAy^i*u","text_ar":"نَبَايِذُ"},{"kind":"text","text":". (A.) ―         -b2-"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"manobuw*apN","text_ar":"مَنْبُوذَةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"and ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"nabiy*apN","text_ar":"نَبِيذَةٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"(assumed tropical:)  A ewe or other animal (L)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"that is not eaten, by reason of its leanness:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(L, K:) so called because it is cast away. (L.) ―         -b3-"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Sal~aY","text_ar":"صَلَّى"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"EalaY qabori manobuw*K","text_ar":"عَلَى قَبْرِ مَنْبُوذٍ"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He"},{"kind":"text","text":"(Mohammad)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"prayed upon the tomb of a foundling:"},{"kind":"text","text":"or, accord. to another reading"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"ElY qaborK manobuw*K","text_ar":"على قَبْرٍ مَنْبُوذٍ"},{"kind":"text","text":", meaning,"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"upon a tomb apart,"},{"kind":"text","text":"(L,) or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"distant,"},{"kind":"text","text":"(K,)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"from other tombs;"},{"kind":"text","text":"(L, K;) like an expression occurring in another trad., ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"mar~a biqaborK munotabi*K","text_ar":"مَرَّ بِقَبْرٍ مُنْتَبِذٍ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"he passed by a tomb apart from other tombs."},{"kind":"text","text":"(L.)"}],"source_refs":["T","S","L","Msb","K","A"]}]},"classical_definitions":null}